Background

		Ms. Mary Ann Tocio serves as the Chairman of Harvard Pilgrim Health Care Inc. Ms. Tocio has been a Director of Bright Horizons Family Solutions, Inc. since November 2001 and Ella Health, Inc. since December 5, 2013. Ms. Tocio has been a Director of Burlington Coat Factory Investments Holdings, Inc. since December 2015. She has been an Independent Director of Harvard Pilgrim Health Care Inc. since 2004 and Civitas Solutions, Inc. since October 1, 2015. She has been a ... Director of Burlington Stores, Inc. since December 22, 2015. She serves as a Director of CareWell Urgent Care and Horizons for Homeless Children. Ms. Tocio served as the Chief Operating Officer of Bright Horizons Family Solutions, Inc. from 1992 to July 2015 and served as its President from June 2000 to June 30, 2015. Ms. Tocio was responsible for all of the Bright Horizons Family Solutions' domestic and global operations. She joined Bright Horizons Inc., in 1992, as Vice President and General Manager of Child Care Operations. Ms. Tocio has dedicated her career in operations management to supporting high-quality services in companies with geographically diverse and decentralized workforces. She served as Chief Operating Officer of Bright Horizons, Inc., from November 1993 to July 1998, which merged with Corporate Family Solutions, Inc. in July 1998 to form Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc. Ms. Tocio has over 30 years of leadership experience. She served in several positions with Wellesley Medical Management, Inc., including as its Senior Vice President of Operations, where she managed ambulatory care centers nationwide from 1983 to 1992. She was responsible for day-to-day operations of the health care units, sales of occupational medical services and the development of affiliation agreements with participating hospitals and corporations. She served as a Director of Mac-Gray Corp. since November 7, 2006. She served as a Director of Telecare Corporation and The George B.H. Macomber Company. She served as a Director of Zany Brainy, Inc. since July 2000. Ms. Tocio received an MBA from Simmons College School of Management.Read Full Background




